# DDAD — Document-Driven AI Development

This project follows DDAD. Documents in `Docs/` are the source of truth; code implements what they specify.

Before writing code:
- Read `Docs/01_product/visao_produto.md` and `Docs/01_product/requisitos_funcionais.md`.
- Check `Docs/02_architecture/` and `Docs/04_governance/registro_decisoes.md` for prior decisions that constrain your approach. Don't contradict a recorded decision without registering a new one that supersedes it.
- Find or create the relevant session (`ddad session create`) and block (`ddad block create`) for the work.

While implementing:
- Generate the execution prompt for a block with `ddad prompt create --block <bloco> --session <sessao>`.
- Generate and fill the closure feedback with `ddad feedback create --block <bloco> --session <sessao>` when the block is done.
- Run `ddad validate` and `ddad audit` to check structural compliance before closing a session.

Do not implement features with no corresponding requirement in `Docs/01_product/requisitos_funcionais.md` — flag the gap instead of silently expanding scope.

See AGENTS.md for the full workflow.
